Comparing the scores per condition

Original paper graph:

Scores per condition of the original paper

Rescorla-Wagner model prediction:

On the left, the average weights for each food group per condition. This average is taken over all trials and all participants. However only the 16 trials in which the food was asked.

Van Hamme-Wasserman model prediction:

Comparing scores over trials for each condition seperately

Condition 0.00

A was either Strawberry or Walnut.
B either Peanut or Peach.
X either Shrimp or Wheat.

Original paper graph:

Scores over all 16 trials (plus a pre measure), condition 0.00)

Note that the pre measure was not taken with the models (since that would just be 0 for all of them). This is also not done in any of the other conditions.

Rescorla-Wagner model prediction:

Van Hamme-Wasserman model prediction:

Condition 0.50

A was either Bran or Horseradish.
B either Cabbage or Lobster.
X either Yogurt or Corn.

Original paper graph:

Scores over all 16 trials (plus a pre measure), condition 0.50

Van Hamme-Wasserman model prediction:

Condition 1.00

A was either Chicken or Cheese.

listY <- list()

listX <- list()
for(i in 1:16){
  df <- as.data.frame(getWM(wm.FR,i))
  df$Trial <- i
  listX<-list.append(listX, df)
